        <div id="article-content" class="article-content">
            <p>Many people set a goal to complete the Quran in just two weeks—whether during Ramadan, on special occasions, or as a personal spiritual challenge. Achieving this requires a well-structured plan, discipline, and consistency. A practical schedule should focus on daily reading targets, optimal recitation times (such as Fajr and Asr), and minimizing distractions. Additionally, using a Quran app for tracking progress and reciting aloud can improve focus and retention. Choosing a 16-line Mushaf and sticking to it ensures consistency throughout the journey.</p>

