            <h3 id="customized-schedule">1. Make a Customized Schedule That Prioritizes Quran Reading</h3>
            <p>A structured schedule is essential for staying on track. Set fixed recitation times that align with your daily routine, such as after Salah, early in the morning, or during quiet periods.</p>
            <p>When planning your schedule, consider:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>The number of hours you can dedicate daily.</li>
                <li>Identifying quiet times with minimal distractions.</li>
                <li>Take short breaks to maintain focus and avoid fatigue.</li>
                <li>Temporarily adjusting non-essential activities to prioritize Quran reading.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>A realistic and clear plan will help you maintain consistency and meet your goal.</p>

            <h3 id="daily-targets">2. Set Clear Daily Reading Targets</h3>
            <p>To complete the Quran in 14 days, you need to read at least 2–3 Juz per day. If breaking down Juz into sections is easier, aim for at least 400+ Ayahs daily. This structured approach makes the goal more manageable.</p>
            <p>A simple breakdown could be:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>2 Juz per day = 15 days completion</li>
                <li>3 Juz per day = 10 days completion (allows extra time for review or catching up)</li>
                <li>100 Ayahs per Salah = 500+ Ayahs daily, completing in two weeks</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Dividing your reading into smaller sessions prevents exhaustion and enhances retention.</p>

            <h3 id="fajr-asr">3. Prioritize Recitations in Fajr and Asr Time</h3>
            <p>The most peaceful and productive times for Quran recitation are early morning (Fajr) and late afternoon (Asr). Allah says, "Establish prayer at the decline of the sun… and at dawn" (Surah Hud: 114).</p>
            <p>During these hours, distractions are minimal, allowing for focused and meaningful recitation. Allocating a significant portion of your daily reading to these times can accelerate your progress.</p>

            <!-- Journey Button -->
